---

<section id="about">
  <div
    class="container grid grid-cols-1 items-start gap-15 md:grid-cols-[280px_1fr]"
  >
    <div
      class="rounded-card border-ink bg-pink shadow-pop aspect-square w-full max-w-[220px] overflow-hidden border-[3px] md:max-w-none"
    >
      <img
        src="/img/profile.jpg"
        alt="Billy Gunawan"
        class="h-full w-full object-cover object-left"
      />
    </div>
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">About me</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">
        Results-driven, AI-assisted, detail-oriented
      </h2>
      <p class="mb-4 max-w-[560px] text-[#5c5470]">
        I'm a software engineer with 6 years of experience designing and
        shipping full-stack products — from real-time stock trading platforms to
        internal CMS tools and monorepo migrations. I lean heavily on
        AI-assisted workflows to move faster without cutting corners, and I
        enjoy untangling gnarly technical problems as much as I enjoy shipping
        clean, maintainable code.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4 max-w-[560px] text-[#5c5470]">
        I've worked across the stack — real-time WebSocket systems, REST APIs,
        monorepo architecture, and everything from pixel-perfect front-ends to
        database design — and I care just as much about developer experience as
        user experience.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-7 flex flex-wrap gap-9">
        <div class="flex flex-col">
          <strong class="font-heading text-purple text-[1.8rem]">6+</strong>
          <span class="text-[0.85rem] text-[#8a8298]">years engineering</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col">
          <strong class="font-heading text-purple text-[1.8rem]">4</strong>
          <span class="text-[0.85rem] text-[#8a8298]">companies & teams</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col">
          <strong class="font-heading text-purple text-[1.8rem]">1,000+</strong>
          <span class="text-[0.85rem] text-[#8a8298]">users served</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
